This extension provides a new `{% defaultmacro %}` statement, which defines a macro only if it does not exist.

For example,

```html+jinja
{% defaultmacro example() %}
    test 123
{% enddefaultmacro %}
```

is equivalent to

```html+jinja
{% macro default_example() %}
test 123
{% endmacro %}
{% if not example %}
    {% macro example() %}
        test 123
    {% endmacro %}
{% endif %}
```

Additionally, the default implementation is also available as `default_$macroname`, which makes it possible
to reference it in the override.

Generate a header id attribute value from the given header
HTML content.

This is only called if the "header-ids" extra is enabled.
Subclasses may override this for different header ids.

@param text {str} The text of the header tag
@param prefix {str} The requested prefix for header ids. This is the
    value of the "header-ids" extra key, if any. Otherwise, None.
@param n {int} (unused) The <hN> tag number, i.e. `1` for an <h1> tag.
@returns {str} The value for the header tag's "id" attribute. Return
    None to not have an id attribute and to exclude this header from
    the TOC (if the "toc" extra is specified).
